//Source
If &FilePath.IsEmpty()
 &HttpResponse.AddString(!"Error!, no hay archivo para descargar")
Else
 &Ext = &FilePath.Trim().Substring((&FilePath.LastIndexOf(".") + 1), &FilePath.Length())
 &NomArch = &FilePath.Trim().Substring((&FilePath.LastIndexOf(&File.Separator) + 1), &FilePath.Length())
 &NomArch = Trim(&NomArch.Replace(' ', '_'))
 
 &ContentType = GetTipArch.Udp(&Ext) //&ContentType = 'application/octet-stream'
 
 &HttpResponse.AddHeader(!"Content-Type", &ContentType)
 &HttpResponse.AddHeader(!"Content-Disposition", "attachment;filename=" + &NomArch)
 &HttpResponse.AddHeader(!"X-Frame-Options", !"deny")
 &HttpResponse.AddHeader(!"Type-Options", !" nosniff")
 &HttpResponse.AddFile(&FilePath)
 
 If &IsDeleteTheFile
  &File.Source = &FilePath
  If &File.Exists()
   &File.Delete()
  EndIf
 EndIf
EndIf

//Parm
Parm(in:&FilePath, in:&IsDeleteTheFile);

//Variables
ContentType  -> Varchar(100)
Ext          -> Varchar(5) 
File         -> File
FilePath     -> Varchar(1K)
HttpResponse -> HttpResponse
IsNoDelete   -> Boolean
NomArch      -> Varchar(1K)

ese es el stored procedure, grabalo como .sql

DECLARE @name NVARCHAR(256) -- database name  
DECLARE @path NVARCHAR(512) -- path for backup files  
DECLARE @fileName NVARCHAR(512) -- filename for backup  
DECLARE @fileDate NVARCHAR(40) -- used for file name
 
-- specify database backup directory
SET @path = 'k:\sqlbackup\'  
 
-- specify filename format
--SELECT @fileDate = CONVERT(NVARCHAR(20),GETDATE(),112) 
SELECT @fileDate = DATENAME(WEEKDAY, GETDATE())
 
DECLARE db_cursor CURSOR READ_ONLY FOR  
SELECT name 
FROM master.sys.databases 
WHERE name NOT IN ('tempdb')  -- exclude these databases
AND state = 0 -- database is online
AND is_in_standby = 0 -- database is not read only for log shipping
 
OPEN db_cursor   
FETCH NEXT FROM db_cursor INTO @name   
 
WHILE @@FETCH_STATUS = 0   
BEGIN   
   SET @fileName = @path + @name + '_' + @fileDate + '.BAK'  
   BACKUP DATABASE @name TO DISK = @fileName WITH INIT
 
   FETCH NEXT FROM db_cursor INTO @name   
END   
 
CLOSE db_cursor   
DEALLOCATE db_cursor
